        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 11 at 8:02PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 800 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Wenona, or 8 miles southwest of Streator, moving northeast at 15
mph. Additional strong thunderstorms were localted over southern and
central LaSalle and western Grundy Counties, also moving northeast
at about 15 mph.

HAZARD...Localized wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Grand Ridge, Oglesby, Ransom, Marseilles, Dayton, Mazon, Tonica,
Kinsman, Streator, Morris, South Streator, Ottawa, Seneca, North
Utica, Kangley, Leonore, Naplate, Lostant, Verona, Cedar Point, Long
Point, Wenona, Carbon Hill, La Salle, and Peru.
</description>
        <instruction>Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. If outdoors,
consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
